+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0123apog4jYvnEdvj649X738","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DrbafdxJKXFk9CMuUC1CkD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-fts-search.md","content":"# Full-Text Search Feature Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Add full-text search using SQLite FTS5 to the existing notes API, with search, suggest, and auto-syncing FTS index.\n\n**Architecture:** Create an FTS5 virtual table (`notes_fts`) that mirrors the `title` and `body` columns of the `notes` table. Use SQLite triggers to keep the FTS index in sync on INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE. Add two new route handlers for search and suggest endpoints in the existing routes file.\n\n**Tech Stack:** SQLite FTS5, better-sqlite3, Express, TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add FTS5 virtual table and triggers to database setup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/db.ts:9-19` (inside `createDatabase` function, after the notes table creation)\n\n**Step 1: Add FTS5 table creation and triggers after the notes table**\n\nAdd the following after the existing `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes` block in `createDatabase()`:\n\n```typescript\n// Create FTS5 virtual table for full-text search\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes_fts USING fts5(\n    title,\n    body,\n    content='notes',\n    content_rowid='id'\n  )\n`);\n\n// Create triggers to keep FTS index in sync\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ai AFTER INSERT ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ad AFTER DELETE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_au AFTER UPDATE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add initial FTS population after seed data insert**\n\nIn `seedDatabase()`, after the `insertMany(notes)` call, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Populate FTS index with seeded data\ndb.exec(`INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) SELECT id, title, body FROM notes`);\n```\n\nThis is needed because the triggers only fire for new inserts AFTER they're created, but `seedDatabase` may be called after `createDatabase` which creates the triggers. Actually, since the triggers ARE created in `createDatabase` before `seedDatabase` is called, the triggers will fire during seed inserts. So we do NOT need manual population. Let me verify the flow:\n\n1. `createDatabase()` creates notes table, then FTS table, then triggers\n2. `seedDatabase()` inserts notes - triggers fire and populate FTS\n\nSo no manual FTS population is needed in `seedDatabase()`.\n\n**Step 3: Run existing tests to verify nothing breaks**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: 15 CRUD tests still pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add search endpoint `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add new route handler before the `return router` statement)\n\n**Step 1: Add imports for SearchResult**\n\nAt top of `src/routes.ts`, update the import:\n```typescript\nimport { Note, NoteInput, SearchResult } from './models.js';\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add search route handler**\n\nAdd before `return router;` in `createRoutes()`:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search - Full-text search\nrouter.get('/notes/search', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const page = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page as string) || 1);\n    const perPage = 20;\n    const offset = (page - 1) * perPage;\n\n    // Sanitize query for FTS5: escape special characters and wrap terms\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q);\n\n    // Count total results\n    const countStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT COUNT(*) as total FROM notes_fts WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n    `);\n    let total: number;\n    try {\n      total = (countStmt.get(sanitized) as { total: number }).total;\n    } catch {\n      // If FTS query syntax is invalid, return empty results\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Get paginated results with ranking and snippets\n    const searchStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes.id,\n        notes.title,\n        snippet(notes_fts, 1, '<mark>', '</mark>', '...', 32) as snippet,\n        rank\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT ? OFFSET ?\n    `);\n\n    let results: SearchResult[];\n    try {\n      results = searchStmt.all(sanitized, perPage, offset) as SearchResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n      total = 0;\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results, total, page, perPage });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add the `sanitizeFtsQuery` helper function**\n\nAdd this function outside `createRoutes` (or at the top of the file, before `createRoutes`):\n\n```typescript\nfunction sanitizeFtsQuery(query: string): string {\n  // If the query contains quoted phrases, pass them through\n  if (query.includes('\"')) {\n    // Remove any FTS5 special operators that could cause errors\n    return query.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%]/g, ' ').replace(/\"/g, '\"').trim() || '\"\"';\n  }\n  // For unquoted queries, escape special chars and wrap each term in quotes\n  // to prevent FTS5 syntax errors\n  const cleaned = query.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%\"']/g, ' ').trim();\n  if (!cleaned) return '\"\"';\n  const terms = cleaned.split(/\\s+/).filter(Boolean);\n  return terms.map(t => `\"${t}\"`).join(' ');\n}\n```\n\n**Important:** The search route MUST be registered BEFORE the `GET /notes/:id` route, otherwise Express will match `/notes/search` as `/notes/:id` with id=\"search\".\n\n**Step 4: Run search tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: Search tests 1-12 and 19-20 should pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add suggest endpoint `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add new route handler)\n\n**Step 1: Add suggest route handler**\n\nAdd after the search route handler:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search/suggest - Autocomplete suggestions\nrouter.get('/notes/search/suggest', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    // Use prefix matching with FTS5\n    const sanitized = q.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%\"']/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [] });\n      return;\n    }\n    const terms = sanitized.split(/\\s+/).filter(Boolean);\n    // Use prefix query: last term gets a * for prefix matching\n    const ftsQuery = terms.map((t, i) => i === terms.length - 1 ? `\"${t}\"*` : `\"${t}\"`).join(' ');\n\n    const stmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT notes.id, notes.title\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT 5\n    `);\n\n    let results: { id: number; title: string }[];\n    try {\n      results = stmt.all(ftsQuery) as { id: number; title: string }[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Ensure route ordering is correct\n\n**Critical:** The search routes (`/notes/search` and `/notes/search/suggest`) must be registered BEFORE the `/notes/:id` route, otherwise Express will match \"search\" as a parameter `:id`.\n\nMove the search and suggest route handlers to be BEFORE `router.get('/notes/:id', ...)` in the routes file.\n\n**Step 1: Verify route order and run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Final validation\n\n**Step 1: Run full test suite**\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass (15 CRUD + 20 search)\n\n**Step 2: Run build**\nRun: `npm run build`\nExpected: No TypeScript compilation errors\n\n**Step 3: Run lint**\nRun: `npm run lint`\nExpected: No linting errors\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16502,"cache_read_input_tokens":21123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16502},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ad2cd8c-a5cd-411a-9141-66b78e77c88d","uuid":"f9c0f596-824a-4876-971f-1443feb47d02"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DrbafdxJKXFk9CMuUC1CkD","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-fts-search.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ad2cd8c-a5cd-411a-9141-66b78e77c88d","uuid":"b89182f6-2f2b-48eb-8843-71bc14ee874e","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-fts-search.md","content":"# Full-Text Search Feature Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Add full-text search using SQLite FTS5 to the existing notes API, with search, suggest, and auto-syncing FTS index.\n\n**Architecture:** Create an FTS5 virtual table (`notes_fts`) that mirrors the `title` and `body` columns of the `notes` table. Use SQLite triggers to keep the FTS index in sync on INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE. Add two new route handlers for search and suggest endpoints in the existing routes file.\n\n**Tech Stack:** SQLite FTS5, better-sqlite3, Express, TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add FTS5 virtual table and triggers to database setup\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/db.ts:9-19` (inside `createDatabase` function, after the notes table creation)\n\n**Step 1: Add FTS5 table creation and triggers after the notes table**\n\nAdd the following after the existing `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes` block in `createDatabase()`:\n\n```typescript\n// Create FTS5 virtual table for full-text search\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes_fts USING fts5(\n    title,\n    body,\n    content='notes',\n    content_rowid='id'\n  )\n`);\n\n// Create triggers to keep FTS index in sync\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ai AFTER INSERT ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_ad AFTER DELETE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n  END\n`);\n\ndb.exec(`\n  CREATE TRIGGER IF NOT EXISTS notes_au AFTER UPDATE ON notes BEGIN\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(notes_fts, rowid, title, body) VALUES('delete', old.id, old.title, old.body);\n    INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) VALUES (new.id, new.title, new.body);\n  END\n`);\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add initial FTS population after seed data insert**\n\nIn `seedDatabase()`, after the `insertMany(notes)` call, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Populate FTS index with seeded data\ndb.exec(`INSERT INTO notes_fts(rowid, title, body) SELECT id, title, body FROM notes`);\n```\n\nThis is needed because the triggers only fire for new inserts AFTER they're created, but `seedDatabase` may be called after `createDatabase` which creates the triggers. Actually, since the triggers ARE created in `createDatabase` before `seedDatabase` is called, the triggers will fire during seed inserts. So we do NOT need manual population. Let me verify the flow:\n\n1. `createDatabase()` creates notes table, then FTS table, then triggers\n2. `seedDatabase()` inserts notes - triggers fire and populate FTS\n\nSo no manual FTS population is needed in `seedDatabase()`.\n\n**Step 3: Run existing tests to verify nothing breaks**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: 15 CRUD tests still pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add search endpoint `GET /notes/search?q=<query>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add new route handler before the `return router` statement)\n\n**Step 1: Add imports for SearchResult**\n\nAt top of `src/routes.ts`, update the import:\n```typescript\nimport { Note, NoteInput, SearchResult } from './models.js';\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add search route handler**\n\nAdd before `return router;` in `createRoutes()`:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search - Full-text search\nrouter.get('/notes/search', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    const page = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page as string) || 1);\n    const perPage = 20;\n    const offset = (page - 1) * perPage;\n\n    // Sanitize query for FTS5: escape special characters and wrap terms\n    const sanitized = sanitizeFtsQuery(q);\n\n    // Count total results\n    const countStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT COUNT(*) as total FROM notes_fts WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n    `);\n    let total: number;\n    try {\n      total = (countStmt.get(sanitized) as { total: number }).total;\n    } catch {\n      // If FTS query syntax is invalid, return empty results\n      res.json({ results: [], total: 0, page, perPage });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Get paginated results with ranking and snippets\n    const searchStmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT\n        notes.id,\n        notes.title,\n        snippet(notes_fts, 1, '<mark>', '</mark>', '...', 32) as snippet,\n        rank\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT ? OFFSET ?\n    `);\n\n    let results: SearchResult[];\n    try {\n      results = searchStmt.all(sanitized, perPage, offset) as SearchResult[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n      total = 0;\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results, total, page, perPage });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 3: Add the `sanitizeFtsQuery` helper function**\n\nAdd this function outside `createRoutes` (or at the top of the file, before `createRoutes`):\n\n```typescript\nfunction sanitizeFtsQuery(query: string): string {\n  // If the query contains quoted phrases, pass them through\n  if (query.includes('\"')) {\n    // Remove any FTS5 special operators that could cause errors\n    return query.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%]/g, ' ').replace(/\"/g, '\"').trim() || '\"\"';\n  }\n  // For unquoted queries, escape special chars and wrap each term in quotes\n  // to prevent FTS5 syntax errors\n  const cleaned = query.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%\"']/g, ' ').trim();\n  if (!cleaned) return '\"\"';\n  const terms = cleaned.split(/\\s+/).filter(Boolean);\n  return terms.map(t => `\"${t}\"`).join(' ');\n}\n```\n\n**Important:** The search route MUST be registered BEFORE the `GET /notes/:id` route, otherwise Express will match `/notes/search` as `/notes/:id` with id=\"search\".\n\n**Step 4: Run search tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: Search tests 1-12 and 19-20 should pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add suggest endpoint `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/routes.ts` (add new route handler)\n\n**Step 1: Add suggest route handler**\n\nAdd after the search route handler:\n\n```typescript\n// GET /notes/search/suggest - Autocomplete suggestions\nrouter.get('/notes/search/suggest', (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {\n  try {\n    const q = req.query.q as string | undefined;\n\n    if (!q || q.trim() === '') {\n      throw new ValidationError('Search query is required');\n    }\n\n    // Use prefix matching with FTS5\n    const sanitized = q.replace(/[*+\\-^~(){}[\\]<>|&!/\\\\:;@#$%\"']/g, ' ').trim();\n    if (!sanitized) {\n      res.json({ results: [] });\n      return;\n    }\n    const terms = sanitized.split(/\\s+/).filter(Boolean);\n    // Use prefix query: last term gets a * for prefix matching\n    const ftsQuery = terms.map((t, i) => i === terms.length - 1 ? `\"${t}\"*` : `\"${t}\"`).join(' ');\n\n    const stmt = db.prepare(`\n      SELECT notes.id, notes.title\n      FROM notes_fts\n      JOIN notes ON notes.id = notes_fts.rowid\n      WHERE notes_fts MATCH ?\n      ORDER BY rank\n      LIMIT 5\n    `);\n\n    let results: { id: number; title: string }[];\n    try {\n      results = stmt.all(ftsQuery) as { id: number; title: string }[];\n    } catch {\n      results = [];\n    }\n\n    res.json({ results });\n  } catch (err) {\n    next(err);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run all tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Ensure route ordering is correct\n\n**Critical:** The search routes (`/notes/search` and `/notes/search/suggest`) must be registered BEFORE the `/notes/:id` route, otherwise Express will match \"search\" as a parameter `:id`.\n\nMove the search and suggest route handlers to be BEFORE `router.get('/notes/:id', ...)` in the routes file.\n\n**Step 1: Verify route order and run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Final validation\n\n**Step 1: Run full test suite**\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All 35 tests pass (15 CRUD + 20 search)\n\n**Step 2: Run build**\nRun: `npm run build`\nExpected: No TypeScript compilation errors\n\n**Step 3: Run lint**\nRun: `npm run lint`\nExpected: No linting errors\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
